# Dashboard UI: Hover Effects Policy

**Glob pattern:** `dashboard/**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,css,html}`

## Core Principle

**Static tiles and cards should NOT have hover effects unless they perform an action or reveal information on hover.**

## Rules

1. **No hover effects on static display cards:**
   - Statistics cards that only show data (e.g., "Total Nodes", "Error Rate", "Avg Duration")
   - Information panels that don't respond to interaction
   - Static metric displays
   - Read-only data containers

2. **Hover effects ARE allowed for:**
   - Interactive buttons (click actions)
   - Clickable cards that navigate or trigger actions
   - Filter/legend items that reveal or filter content on hover/click
   - Expandable sections (details/summary elements)
   - Cards that show tooltips or additional info on hover

3. **Implementation:**
   - Remove `hover:` classes from static cards
   - Remove `transition-all` or `transition-*` from static cards (unless needed for other animations)
   - Keep hover effects only on interactive elements
   - Use `cursor-pointer` only for clickable elements

## Examples

**❌ Bad (static card with hover):**
```html
<div class="stat-card hover:border-primary-500 hover:bg-slate-800">
  <div>Total Nodes: 78</div>
</div>
```

**✅ Good (static card without hover):**
```html
<div class="stat-card">
  <div>Total Nodes: 78</div>
</div>
```

**✅ Good (interactive card with hover):**
```html
<button class="card hover:border-primary-500 cursor-pointer" onclick="doAction()">
  Click to filter
</button>
```

## CSS Classes

- `.stat-card` - Should NOT have hover effects (static display)
- `.card-elevated` - Check usage: if used for static containers, remove hover; if interactive, keep hover
- Interactive elements - Keep hover effects for better UX
